Defendant Lemetrius Quondale Smith in court with Attorney Martin R. Tanz.  Defendant Lemetrius Quondale Smith in custody.  Catelin Ringersma appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  AS TO COUNT #1:  The Court imposed the following sentence:  The Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be SIXTY (60) months consecutive to any other sentence.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for THIRTY (30) months with credit for 316 days time served.  Defendant shall serve THIRTY (30) months on EXTENDED SUPERVISION.  

The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.
The defendant is not eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  

The Court advised the defendant of the determinate sentence pursuant to statute and in accordance with Form CR-234.  Copy provided to defendant. 

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
 - No controlled substances or alcohol;
 - AODA assessment; treatment, if needed;
 - Random urine screens to ensure compliance;
 - Any counseling deemed appropriate by the Department;
 - No contact with victims and the location of Jynx Nightclub;
 - Restitution set at ZERO.
 - Pay the DNA surcharge, costs and disbursements. Court ordered monies taken by the Department of Correction from up to 25% of prison funds.  Balance would be then be paid while on Extended Supervision.  If not paid, will convert to a civil judgment.   

